10) PRICES (DOLLARS) VS STRIPE AMOUNTS (CENTS) — CRITICAL NUANCE

DB product prices are stored in dollars (`NUMERIC(12,2)`).
Use `formatMoney(value)` directly. Never convert DB prices.

Stripe amounts are in cents.
When inserting `invoices.total_amount` (numeric dollars), convert cents → dollars exactly once.

Never apply the “no conversion” rule to Stripe’s amount values.

